Reasoning: The paper deals with network flow problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and graph theory. Specifically, the paper considers single-sink network flow problems with different types of flows (unsplittable, confluent, and priority) and examines their approximability. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.NE (networking and internet architecture), cs.GT (computer science and game theory), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), and cs.CC (computational complexity). Among these, cs.DS and cs.NE seem to be the most likely categories, as they are directly related to network flow problems and their algorithms. However, the paper also involves some theoretical analysis of the approximability of these problems, which could make cs.GT, cs.DM, and cs.CC relevant as well.
